where R1 is a hydrophobic moiety of alkyl, alkenyl, cycloalkyl, alkylarylalkyl, alkoxyalkyl, alkylaminoalkyl or alkylamidoalkyl. R1 has from about 8 to about 30 carbon atoms and may be straight or branched chained and saturated or unsaturated. Examples of long chain alkyl groups include, but are not limited to, octadecenyl (oleyl), octadecyl (stearyl), docosenoic (erucyl) and the derivatives of tallow, coco, soy and rapeseed oils;
